sql:
SELECT name, median_household_income, population_density
FROM counties
WHERE median_household_income > (SELECT AVG(median_household_income) FROM counties);

external_knowledge:
- "Wealthy counties" refers to counties with the highest median household income;
- "Top 5 by median household income" means the top 5 counties when ranked by their median household income in descending order;
- "Highest population" means the county with the largest population within each of the top 5 income ranks.

- Population density is the number of people per unit area of land;
- A state can be metaphorically thought of as a garden, and counties as patches of land within this garden;
- The average population density gives an idea of how crowded or sparse the patches (counties) are within each garden (state).

- 'crown jewels of prosperity' refers to the counties with the highest median household income within their respective states;
